All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddEmployeeController
    The AddEmployeeController class is used to add a new employee to the database.
    AddTaskController
    The AddTaskController is responsible for adding tasks to the database that will be shown on the dashboard.
    CompleteTaskController
    The Complete
    DashboardController
    The DashboardController handles all activities on the dashboard including: completing tasks, adding tasks, removing tasks, refreshing the tasks, viewing selected task details, and viewing the history of completed tasks.
    Details
    The Details class is used to retrieve the details of a task from the database.
    Employee
    The Employee class handles all related fields corresponding to an employee.
    GlobalVariables
    The GlobalVariables class is used to transfer information screen to screen seamlessly.
    Login
    The Login class is used to verify the username and password combination entered on the landing screen.
    LoginController
    The LoginController handles the operations that are performed on the landing screen.
    Main
    The Main class that runs first in any program
    Tasks
    The Tasks class is responsible for handling the tasks created and displayed on the dashboard.
    ViewDetailsController
    The ViewDetailsController handles showing the details of a selectedTask from the dashboard.
    ViewHistoryController
    The ViewHistoryController is responsible for displaying the contents of the maintenance_history.txt file to the JFXTextArea.
